# The problem is that state_wrapper has an outer feature String which means that this could have many different types depending on the actual String this is used in.
# However, here this is always called on String.this, so there should IMHO be no problem. Furthermore, it is strange that this is reported during the DFA phase only.

a is
  s is
  q =>
    _ := t s
  t(p T) => p

B ref : a is
_ := B.q
